==English==
===Etymology===
[[Greek]] ''(kryptos)'' + [[Latin]] ''-[[ides]].'' (Eng. usg. 1983; coined by John E. Wall in the ''ISC Newsletter'')
===Nouns===
# (''cryptozoologically'') Any [[creature]] that may or may not exist.  Cryptids are hypothetical creatures that have been "sighted" or [[seen]], but are not proven real.

